  <h1>Coral Documentation</h1>

  <p>
    Welcome to the Coral documentation! Coral is a production-ready neural network weight
    versioning system that provides git-like version control for ML model weights.
  </p>

  <h2>What is Coral?</h2>

  <p>
    Coral ("git for neural networks") offers:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Lossless Delta Encoding</strong> - Store similar weights as deltas with perfect reconstruction</li>
    <li><strong>Git-like Version Control</strong> - Full branching, committing, merging, and tagging workflow</li>
    <li><strong>Content-Addressable Storage</strong> - Automatic deduplication via SimHash and LSH</li>
    <li><strong>Training Integration</strong> - Seamless PyTorch and Lightning callbacks</li>
    <li><strong>Cloud Storage</strong> - S3-compatible backend with push/pull/sync</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Quick Install</h2>

  <pre><code># Install from PyPI
pip install coral-ml

# With PyTorch support
pip install coral-ml[torch]

# With all optional dependencies
pip install coral-ml[all]</code></pre>

  <h2>Basic Usage</h2>

  <pre><code>from coral import Repository, WeightTensor
from coral.core.weight_tensor import WeightMetadata
import numpy as np

# Initialize repository
repo = Repository("./my_model", init=True)

# Create and stage weights
weight = WeightTensor(
    data=np.random.randn(256, 128).astype(np.float32),
    metadata=WeightMetadata(
        name="layer1.weight",
        shape=(256, 128),
        dtype=np.float32
    )
)

repo.stage_weights({"{"}layer1.weight": weight{"}"})
commit = repo.commit("Initial model weights")

# Create branches for experiments
repo.create_branch("experiment")
repo.checkout("experiment")</code></pre>

